22
00:00:59,288 --> 00:01:05,090
It's a quick review of the housing code recently was updated, hadn't been updated in quite a few years.

23
00:01:05,331 --> 00:01:09,572
And as of April, the new housing code is in effect.

24
00:01:10,293 --> 00:01:11,453
And there's a few changes.

25
00:01:11,553 --> 00:01:16,875
Some of it, they just updated some language and made it more, you know, with the time, so to speak.

26
00:01:18,036 --> 00:01:21,917
But one of the changes to the new housing code is around the heating season.

27
00:01:23,278 --> 00:01:27,400
In the old housing code, the heating season went till June 15th.

28
00:01:29,117 --> 00:01:33,581
The new housing code moves it back to May 31st.

29
00:01:34,862 --> 00:01:49,753
In the past, if a building landlord wanted to push back the heating season even further, they would all have to come to the board and ask for an individual variance for each of them.

30
00:01:50,674 --> 00:01:56,398
Per request, we would have to vote on and approve individual variances.

31
00:02:00,170 --> 00:02:18,446
Housing Code allows that a Board of Health may alter the heating season as defined in 105 CMR 410-180A by ending it no earlier than May 15th or delaying the start date to no later than September 30th.

32
00:02:20,356 --> 00:02:30,302
in a particular year for all residences within its jurisdiction, just by posting the notice of such alteration on the municipality's website.

33
00:02:31,182 --> 00:02:40,528
The Board of Health's decision to alter the heating season shall not be required to conform to the provisions for the granting of individual variances required by 105 CMR 410-700.

34
00:02:40,548 --> 00:02:42,229
So we do have with us today both Mystic Place and 99 Riverside,

35
00:02:50,361 --> 00:03:02,994
Avenue, who had already inquired, especially when we had that little bit of a heat wave a while ago, a couple, a week or so ago, about seeking a variance to move the heating season back.

